\pard\f0\fs28   ({\b a}) Subsp. {\b sibirica}: Stems simple, solitary, branched at the apex. Appendages lanceolate, reticulate and ciliate, usually shorter than the ovary. Corolla 17-25 mm. {\i Throughout the range of the species}.
\par 

\pard\f0\fs28   ({\b b}) Subsp. {\b taurica} (Juz.) Fedorov,{\i  Bot. Jour. Linn. Soc.}{\b  67}: 281 (1973) ({\i C. taurica} Juz.): Stems numerous, the central thicker and more robust than the others. Appendages lanceolate, not reticulate, usually shorter than the ovary. Corolla 15-20 mm.{\i  Krym}.
\par 

\pard\f0\fs28   ({\b c}) Subsp. {\b talievii} (Juz.) Fedorov,{\i  loc. cit.} (1973) ({\i C. talievii} Juz.): Stems 5-10(-20) cm, ascending. Appendages broadly lanceolate, as long as or longer than the ovary. Corolla c. 30 mm.{\i  • Mountains of Krym.}
\par 

\pard\f0\fs28   ({\b d}) Subsp. {\b elatior} (Fomin) Fedorov, {\i loc. cit.} (1973) ({\i C. sibirica} f.{\i  elatior} Fomin): Stem 30-60 cm, simple, solitary, 3-5 mm in diameter, setose-hairy. Appendages broadly lanceolate, as long as or longer than the ovary. Corolla 20-30 mm, tubular-infundibuliform.{\i  Ukraine and S. Russia}.
\par 

\pard\f0\fs28   ({\b e}) Subsp. {\b divergentiformis} (Jáv.) Domin,{\i  Preslia}{\b  13-15}: 222 (1936): stem C. 60 cm, hairy, 3-5 mm in diameter. Appendages broadly lanceolate, as long as or longer than the ovary. Corolla 20-40 mm, campanulate. •{\i  Balkan peninsula, Italy, Hungary, Czechoslovakia}.
\par 

\pard\f0\fs28   ({\b f}) Subsp. {\b charkeviczii} (Fedorov) Fedorov,{\i  Bot. Jour. Linn. Soc.}{\b  67}: 281 (1973) ({\i C. charkeviczii} Fedorov): stems numerous, 20-40 cm, 15-20 mm in diameter, hairy, striate, purple. Appendages broadly lanceolate, as long as or longer than the ovary. Corolla c. 30 mm. •{\i  Mountains of Krym.}
\par 

\par 

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 51. C. incurva} Aucher ex A. DC. in DC.,{\i  Prodr.}{\b  7}: 464 (1839). Biennial. Stem erect, pubescent, usually paniculately branched. Leaves pubescent, ovate or ovate-oblong, crenate; basal cordate at the base, petiolate; cauline shortly petiolate, the uppermost sessile. Calyx-teeth broadly triangular-ovate. Appendages ovate, as long as the ovary. Corolla up to 40 mm, pale blue-lilac. 2n = 32.{\i  Scrub and rocky places. • E. Greece. }Gr.
\par 

\par 

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 52. C. grossekii} Heuffel,{\i  Flora} ({\i Regensb}.){\b  16}: 353 (1833). Hispid perennial. Stem up to 70 cm, simple or sometimes branched, angular. Basal leaves cordate, triangular, coarsely 2-serrate, long-petiolate; cauline shortly petiolate, narrower, the uppermost lanceolate, rounded at the base, sessile. Flowers pedicellate in a paniculately branched inflorescence. Calyx-teeth setose-ciliate, lanceolate; appendages lanceolate, shorter than the teeth. Corolla 20-30 mm, hirsute, campanulate, violet, 2-3 times as long as calyx-teeth. {\i Rocky places in woods. • C. part of Balkan peninsula and S. Romania.} Bu Ju Rm.
\par 

\par 

