\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 53. C. lanata} Friv.,{\i  Flora} ({\i Regensb}.) {\b 19}: 434 (1836). Biennial.Stems numerous, 30-70 cm, villous, erect or flexuous, branched from the base. Leaves broadly ovate-cordate, serrate, sericeous-tomentose; basal subacute, long-petiolate; upper cauline very small, almost sessile. Flowers subsessile in a many-flowered inflorescence. Calyx-teeth wide, triangular, acuminate; appendages as long as the ovary. Corolla 20-25 mm, broadly campanulate, yellowish-white. Corolla-lobes bearded inside, about twice as long as calyx.{\i  Mountain rocks. • W. & C. Bulgaria, S.E. Jugoslavia.} Bu Ju.
\par 

\par 

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 54. C. dichotoma} L.,{\i  Cent. Pl.}{\b  2}: 10 (1756). Patent-hispid annual. Stem c. 10-15 cm, erect, dichotomously branched. Leaves oblong to ovate, acute, denticulate or entire, sessile. Flowers axillary, solitary. Pedicels short. Calyx-teeth triangular-lanceolate, acuminate, widened at the base, longer than the ovary; appendages lanceolate, longer than the ovary. Corolla c. 20 mm, tubular-campanulate, subglabrous, blue-lilac, twice as long as calyx.{\i  Mediterranean region.} Bl ?Gr Hs It Si.
\par 

\par 

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 55. C. alpestris} All.,{\i  Auct. Syn. Stirp. Horti Taur. }11 (1773) ({\i C. allionii} Vill.). Perennial. Stem simple, usually 1-flowered, sparsely hairy. Basal leaves rosulate, ciliate, linear-lanceolate, subentire, obtuse; cauline linear. Calyx-teeth linear, acuminate, half as long as corolla; appendages ovate, acute, ciliate, 1/3 as long as the teeth. Corolla 30-45 mm, campanulate, distinctly narrowed at base; lobes short, suborbicular, shortly acuminate. 2n = 34.{\i  Stony places. • S.W. Alps.} Ga It.
\par 

\par 

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 56. C. oreadum} Boiss. & Heldr. in Boiss.,{\i  Diagn. Pl. Or. Nov.}{\b  3}({\b 3}): 107 (1856). Caespitose, appressed-hispid, greyish perennial. Stem c. 10 cm, slender, flexuous, fragile, 1-flowered or sparsely branched and 2- to 5-flowered. Basal leaves oblong-spathulate, entire, obtuse, petiolate; cauline oblong-linear, sessile, acute. Flowers long-pedicellate. Calyx-teeth velutinous, lanceolate, acute; appendages very short. Corolla 20-35 mm, blue, narrowly campanulate, hirsute on the veins, 3 times as long as calyx. 2n = 34.{\i  Mountain rocks. • E. Greece} ({\i Olimbos}). Gr.
\par 

\par 

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 57. C. calaminthifolia} Lam.,{\i  Encycl. Méth. Bot.}{\b  1}: 585 (1785). Shortly appressed-pubescent, greyish perennial. Rhizome stout. Stems 10-15 cm, decumbent, numerous, leafy, 3- to 5-flowered, simple, or shortly branched from the middle; branches 1- to 3-flowered. Leaves somewhat succulent; basal rosulate, oblong-spathulate, obtuse, subentire, shortly petiolate; cauline subsessile, ovate-orbicular, usually weakly undulate and obsoletely crenate-dentate. Leaves of the branches very small, elliptical. Flowers shortly pedicellate. Calyx-teeth triangular, subacute; appendages triangular, acute, 1/3 as long as the ovary. Corolla c. 10 mm, blue, tomentose, tubular-infundibuliform, 2½ times as long as calyx. Style exserted. •{\i   Aegean region.} Gr.
\par 

\par 

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 58. C. hierapetrae} Rech. fil.,{\i  Österr. Bot. Zeitschr.}{\b  84}: 170 (1935). Velutinous perennial. Stock stout. Stems c. 5-10 cm, ascending or decumbent, filiform, leafy. Basal leaves 8-10 mm, ovate-spathulate, petiolate; cauline ovate or suborbicular, shortly petiolate. Flowers 1-4. Calyx-teeth triangular, twice as long as the ovary; appendages very short. Corolla 12-15 mm, 2-3 times as long as calyx, infundibuliform. Style exserted.{\i  Rocks. • E. Kriti.} Cr.
\par 

\par 

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 59. C. amorgina} Rech. fil.,{\i  Beih. Bot. Centr. }{\b 54}({\b B}): 646 (1936). Almost glabrous perennial. Stock stout. Stems 3-10 cm, slender, ascending or decumbent, leafy. Leaves 4-6 mm, obovate, shortly petiolate or sessile. Flowers few, terminal. Calyx-teeth triangular, acute, twice as long as the obconical, ribbed ovary; appendages very short. Corolla 6-7 mm, tubular-infundibuliform, 3-4 times as long as calyx. Style exserted.{\i  Limestone rock-crevices. • Kikladhes} ({\i Amorgos}). Gr.
